Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State has been lauded for the timely and proactive steps taken so far by the government on the coronavirus outbreak in Lagos state. The renowned socio-political activist, Chief Adesunbo Onitiri said Sanwo-Olu deserves to be commended for the positive action by all Lagos residents. He said, “The Lagos State Government can still do more as Lagosians deserve more. No doubt the disease is a serious and deadly one that deserves serious attention. “We implore the Governor to ensure that necessary drugs and preventive equipment are provided in all our hospitals in the state.” According to Onitiri, there is need for improved health standards in the collection and disposal of wastes in the state. “All drainages should be well cleaned and kept in good sanitation.  The government should improve on good potable water for the citizens. There should be aggressive public enlightenment on sanitation.” He urged the government to provide sanitizer, face masks and gloves free in all government hospitals, public schools and public centres among others. Onitiri added that all flights coming from China should not be allowed to land in Lagos, so as to protect all Lagosians from the scourge of Coronavirus disease, urging Lagosians to abide by the government’s instructions not to panic but wash their hands more regularly and keep their environment very clean always. 